name: analyzer
desc: Tools for analyzing the protocol files of a Serverpod project.

name: ClassDefinition
desc:
A representation of a yaml file in the protocol directory defining a class
or exception.

name: documentation
desc: The documentation of this class, line by line.

name: fields
desc: The fields of this class / exception.

name: isIdColumn
desc: Whether the column is the default primary key column.

name: isIntSerialIdColumn
desc: Whether the column is a primary key of type int serial.

name: isVectorColumn
desc: Whether the column is of a vector type.

name: EndpointsAnalyzer
desc: Analyzes dart files for the protocol specification.

name: EndpointsAnalyzer.new
desc:
Create a new EndpointsAnalyzer, containing a
AnalysisContextCollection that analyzes all dart files in the
provided directory.

name: analyze
desc: Analyze all files in the AnalysisContextCollection.

name: updateFileContexts
desc: Inform the analyzer that the provided filePaths have been updated.

name: EnumDefinition
desc: A representation of a yaml file in the protocol directory defining an enum.

name: EnumDefinition.new
desc: Create a new EnumDefinition.

name: defaultValue
desc: The default value of the enum when parsing of the enum fails.

name: documentation
desc: The documentation for this enum, line by line.

name: serialized
desc: The type of serialization this enum should use.

name: values
desc:
All the values of the enum.
This also contains possible documentation for them.

name: ExceptionClassDefinition
desc: A ClassDefinition specialization that represents an exception.

name: ExceptionClassDefinition.new
desc: Create a new ExceptionClassDefinition.

name: GeneratorConfig
desc: The configuration of the generation and analyzing process.

name: clientPackagePathParts
desc: Path parts to the client package.

name: dartClientDependsOnServiceClient
desc: True, if dart client depends on the package:serverpod_service_client.

name: dartClientPackage
desc: The name of the client package.

name: enabledFeatures
desc: All the features that are enabled in the serverpod project.

name: extraClasses
desc:
User defined class names for complex types.
Useful for types used in caching and streams.

name: generatedDartClientModelPathParts
desc: The path parts to the protocol directory in the dart client package.

name: generatedServeModelPackagePathParts
desc:
The internal package path parts of the directory, where the generated code is stored in the
server package.

name: generatedServeModelPathParts
desc:
The path parts of the directory, where the generated code is stored in the
server package.

name: generatedServerEndpointDescriptionFilePathParts
desc: The path parts of the generated protocol file.

name: generatedServerEndpointFilePathParts
desc: The path parts of the generated endpoint file.

name: generatedServerProtocolFilePathParts
desc: The path parts of the generated protocol file.

name: libSourcePathParts
desc: Path parts to the lib folder of the server package.

name: load
desc: Create a new GeneratorConfig by loading the configuration in the serverRootDir.

name: modelSourcePathParts
desc: Path parts to the lib/src/models directory of the server package.

name: modules
desc: All the modules defined in the config (of type module).

name: modulesAll
desc: All the modules including my self and internal modules.

name: modulesDependent
desc: All the modules excluding my self

name: name
desc: The name of the serverpod project.

name: protocolSourcePathParts
desc: Path parts to the lib/src/protocol directory of the server package.

name: relativeModelSourcePathParts
desc: Relative path parts to the model directory

name: relativeProtocolSourcePathParts
desc: Relative path parts to the protocol directory

name: serverPackage
desc: The name of the server package.

name: serverPackageDirectoryPathParts
desc:
The parts of the path where the server package is located at.
Might be relative.

name: srcSourcePathParts
desc: Path parts to the lib/src folder of the server package.

name: toString
desc: A string representation of this object.

name: type
desc: The PackageType of the package this GeneratorConfig describes.

name: createMigration
desc:
Creates a new migration version.
If tag is specified, the migration will be tagged with the given name.
If force is true, the migration will be created even if there are
warnings.
If write is false, the migration will not be written to disk.

name: repairMigration
desc:
Creates a repair migration that will bring the database up to date with
the targeted migration version.

name: ModelClassDefinition
desc: A ClassDefinition specialization that represents a model class.

name: ModelClassDefinition.new
desc: Create a new ModelClassDefinition.

name: childClasses
desc: If set to a List of InheritanceDefinitions the class is a parent class and stores the child classes.

name: descendantClasses
desc:
Returns a list of all descendant classes.
This includes all child classes and their descendants.
If the class has no child classes, an empty list is returned.

name: everyParentIsSealed
desc:
Returns true if all parent classes are sealed.
Returns true if the class does not have a parent class.

name: extendsClass
desc: If set to InheritanceDefinitions the class extends another class and stores the ClassDefinition of it's parent.

name: fieldsIncludingInherited
desc:
Returns a list of all fields in this class, including inherited fields.
It ensures that the 'id' field, if present, is always included at the beginning of the list.

name: idField
desc:
Returns the SerializableModelFieldDefinition of the 'id' field.
If the field is not present, an error is thrown.

name: indexes
desc:
The indexes that should be created for the table tableName representing
this class.

name: inheritedFields
desc:
Returns a list of all fields in the parent class.
If there is no parent class, an empty list is returned.

name: isParentClass
desc: Returns true if this class is a parent class or sealed.

name: isSealed
desc: If set to true the class is sealed.

name: isSealedTopNode
desc: Returns true if this class is the top node of a sealed hierarchy.

name: parentClass
desc:
Returns the ModelClassDefinition of the parent class.
If there is no parent class, null is returned.

name: sealedTopNode
desc:
Returns the top node of the sealed hierarchy. If the class is the top node it returns itself.
If the class is not part of a sealed hierarchy, null is returned.

name: tableName
desc:
If set, the name of the table, this class should be stored in, in the
database.

name: ModelFieldScopeDefinition
desc: The scope of a field.

name: values
desc: A constant List of the values in this enum, in order of their declaration.

name: PackageType
desc: The type of the package.

name: values
desc: A constant List of the values in this enum, in order of their declaration.

name: ProtocolDefinition
desc:
Defines a projects protocol.
This does not include stuff the ProtocolYamlFileAnalyzer analyzed.

name: ProtocolDefinition.new
desc: Create a new ProtocolDefinition.

name: endpoints
desc:
The endpoints that are a part of this protocol.
This does not include endpoints from other modules or package:serverpod.

name: SerializableModelAnalyzer
desc: Used to analyze a singe yaml model file.

name: extractModelDefinition
desc: Best effort attempt to extract a model definition from a yaml file.

name: resolveModelDependencies
desc: Resolves dependencies between models, this method mutates the input.

name: validateYamlDefinition
desc: Validates a yaml file against an expected syntax for model files.

name: SerializableModelDefinition
desc:
An abstract representation of a yaml file in the
protocol directory.

name: fileRef
desc: Generate the file reference String to this file.

name: SerializableModelFieldDefinition
desc: Describes a single field of a ClassDefinition.

name: SerializableModelFieldDefinition.new
desc: Create a new SerializableModelFieldDefinition.

name: documentation
desc: The documentation of this field, line by line.

name: hasDefaults
desc: returns true if one of the defaults its not null

name: hasOnlyDatabaseDefaults
desc: returns true if only has database default

name: hiddenSerializableField
desc:
Returns true, if this is serialized field that should be hidden.
serverCode specifies if it's code on the server or client side.

name: indexes
desc: Indexes that this field is part of.

name: isSymbolicRelation
desc:
Returns true, if this field has a relation pointer to/from another field
with relation type ForeignRelationDefinition. This means that this field
relation does not propagate to the database, but instead is managed by
the other field.

name: name
desc: The name of the field.

name: relation
desc:
If set the field is a relation to another table. The type of the relation
ForeignRelationDefinition, ObjectRelationDefinition or ListRelationDefinition
determines where and how the relation is stored.

name: scope
desc:
The scope of the field.
It tells us if the field should only be present
in a certain context.

name: shouldIncludeField
desc:
Returns true, if classes should include this field.
serverCode specifies if it's a code on the server or client side.

name: shouldSerializeField
desc:
Returns true, if this field should be added to the serialization.
serverCode specifies if it's code on the server or client side.

name: shouldSerializeFieldForDatabase
desc:
Returns true, if this field should be added to the serialization for the
database.
serverCode specifies if it's code on the server or client side.
This method should only be called for server side code.

name: type
desc: The type of the field.

name: SerializableModelIndexDefinition
desc: The definition of an index for a file, that is also stored in the database.

name: SerializableModelIndexDefinition.new
desc: Create a new SerializableModelIndexDefinition.

name: fields
desc:
The fields this index includes.
The order of the fields matters.

name: isVectorIndex
desc: Whether the index is of vector type.

name: name
desc: The name of the index.

name: parameters
desc: The parameters of the index, if any. Used for Vector indexes.

name: type
desc:
The type of this index.
Usually this is btree.

name: unique
desc: Whether the fields of this index should be unique.

name: vectorDistanceFunction
desc: The vector index distance function, if it is a vector index.

name: SupportedIdType
desc:
Supported ID type definitions.
All configuration to support other types is done only on this class. A
supported id type is a combination of a type and a default value. It is
possible to support multiple default values for a same type (e.g. uuid type
with default of versions 4 and 7), with each having its getter. For new
entries, add a new static getter and update the all getter. If the entry
contains a type not yet used by existing id types, it's necessary to update
the Table constructor at packages:serverpod/src/database/concepts/table.dart.

name: aliases
desc:
The aliases for the id type as exposed to the user. Supports multiple,
even though it is not recommended to use more than one to avoid confusion.

name: all
desc: All supported id types.

name: defaultValue
desc:
The default value for the column on the database definition. Must be one
of the supported defaults for the type.

name: fromString
desc:
Get the SupportedIdType from a valid string alias. If the input is
invalid, will throw a FormatException.

name: int
desc: Id type that generates sequential integer values.

name: type
desc: The supported id type.

name: userOptions
desc: All aliases exposed to the user.

name: uuidV4
desc: Id type that generates UUID v4 values.

name: uuidV7
desc: Id type that generates UUID v7 values.

name: TypeDefinition
desc: Contains information about the type of fields, arguments and return values.

name: TypeDefinition.fromDartType
desc:
Creates an TypeDefinition from a given DartType.
throws FromDartTypeClassNameException if the class name could not be
determined.

name: TypeDefinition.mixedUrlAndClassName
desc:
Creates an TypeDefinition from mixed where the url
and className is separated by ':'.

name: applyProtocolReferences
desc:
Applies protocol references. This makes the protocol: prefix optional.
First, the protocol definition is parsed, then it's check for the
protocol: prefix in types. Whenever no url is set and user specified a
class/enum with the same symbol name it defaults to the protocol: prefix.

name: asNamedRecordField
desc: Returns this TypeDefinition as a named record field

name: asNonNullable
desc: Get this TypeDefinition, but non nullable.

name: asNullable
desc: Get this TypeDefinition, but nullable.

name: className
desc: The class name of the type.

name: columnType
desc: Get the Column extending class name representing this TypeDefinition.

name: customClass
desc: True if this type references a custom class.

name: databaseType
desc: Get the pgsql type that represents this TypeDefinition in the database.

name: databaseTypeEnum
desc:
Get the enum name of the ColumnType, representing this TypeDefinition
in the database.

name: defaultValueType
desc: Returns DefaultValueAllowedType only for fields that are allowed to have defaults

name: generateDeserialization
desc: Generates the constructors for List and Map types

name: generics
desc: The generics the type has.

name: int
desc:
A convenience variable for getting a TypeDefinition of a non null int
quickly.

name: nullable
desc: Whether this type is nullable.

name: projectModelDefinition
desc:
Populated if type is a model that is defined in the project. I.e. not a
module or serverpod model.

name: recordFieldName
desc: The name of the field when used as a named record field.

name: reference
desc: Generate a Reference from this definition.

name: retrieveGenericType
desc:
Retrieves the generic from this type.
Throws a FormatException if no generic is found.

name: toString
desc: A string representation of this object.

name: uuid
desc:
A convenience variable for getting a TypeDefinition of a non null
UuidValue quickly.

name: valueType
desc: converts 'className' string value to ValueType

name: vectorDimension
desc:
Stores the dimension of Vector type (e.g., 1536 for Vector(1536)).
Only populated for Vector types.
